\par Stuart:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3228552\charrsid3228552 
Oh yes, of course. Kingston, at that stage nearly half the population of Jamaica was living in Kingston and its environment, so it was a colonial metropolis, but it was not provincial in the most obvious way. Full of variety, full of street life, full of
 different kinds of people, full of the unemployed and the shops, and the slums. It wasn\rquote 
t a pretty place, but it was full of life. Full of life. And if only I could have hooked creatively into that at that stage, I would never have left. But funnily enough, I had to leave to make contact with it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
