\par Stuart:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3228552\charrsid3228552 Yes. Because of all of what I\rquote 
ve told you about my alternative curriculum, most of those things were happening elsewhere. Langston Hughes was happening in New Yor
k, Yes? American writers were going to Paris, American jazz players were playing in Paris. T.S. Eliot was in London, Ezra Pound was in London, Stravinsky was playing in Europe. So you have to go to see that world! I couldn\rquote 
t be boxed out of that world. I didn\rquote t feel I could fully create that where I was. It wasn\rquote t that I wanted to be English (LAUGHS), I knew I never wanted to be English. I never wanted to be English all my life. I don\rquote 
t want to be European, but I wanted to know about a wider framework of ideas and artistic expressions and political aspirations and theoretical concerns and so on, I just wanted that breadth of reference. So that\rquote s when I thought, \'93You\rquote 
re going to have to go. You\rquote ll come back, of course. Of course. But you have to go. You have to go. You have to be displaced from it in order to make contact with it, because you don\rquote t have access to it in a more direct and authentic way\'94
. My life has consisted of - do you play chess? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7739222\charrsid7739222 
