\par Stuart:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3228552\charrsid3228552 I don\rquote t play chess, but it\rquote s the knight\rquote s move! Yes? That\rquote 
s my life. To get to something, you always move sideways and then advance, you do not go straight to it. So the small memoir that I\rquote m working on is called \'93Displacements\'94, because if you think about the things I\rquote 
ve told you, each of them,
 I felt I was blocked from just being it, but I wanted to get to it. So you had to find another route, find a book which took you back, or an artist that took you back, or a scene in the Jamaican countryside that took you back, or go into a market. Someth
ing had to mediate the experience to me, and one of those was coming abroad. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7739222\charrsid7739222 
