sic. I love folk songs. Remember, this is before the explosion of Jamaican music. It\rquote s very important to say this, because people don\rquote 
t imagine - the classic Jamaican music, at that stage, was folk songs, and a kind of mento, yes, which is a combination of
 African rhythm and minuets, yes? There was no, reggae, sca, blue beat, all of that comes with Independence. This is 12 years before Independence. I came in 1951, Jamaica\rquote s not Independent until 1962. [INTERRUPTION] }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
