t what it is now, garrison areas and tribal political warfare, it wasn\rquote t that, but there were places where if you were a young, brown, middle-class boy, you wouldn\rquote t venture like tha
t. But I moved into much lower, much more indigenous Jamaican kinds of families and homes, with my friends, than I would ever have met through my family and their upper middle-class connections. That\rquote 
s how I - and besides which, as you know, Jamaica is a very small place! }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7739222\charrsid7739222 
