\par Stuart:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3228552\charrsid3228552 But, I mean, in some ways that is a problem I\rquote ve worked on for the rest of my life! (LAUGHS) That is, in sum, what 
I spend my life doing \endash  what\rquote s happened to them; how they\rquote ve changed; how they\rquote re treated; how other people regard them; what\rquote 
s their fate? What have they left behind? What have they added? Have they survived? How have they survived? And although I\rquote ve not 
necessarily written about that directly, that has been the sort of thematic because it connected so much with this kind of social world I was trying to understand, with the personal world, subjective world, which I had experienced. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7739222\charrsid7739222 
