\par Stuart:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3228552\charrsid3228552 At The Royal Court.
 So the Club became a kind of focal centre. The first group was in London. We went from hotel to hotel. Eventually we took root in 100 Oxford Street, which was a jazz club, famous jazz club, but on Monday nights no jazz was played, so Universities and Lef
t
 Review Club moved in there amidst the technical lighting of a jazz club, and there we invited all the people that we felt - Richard Crossman, Crosland, we debated with Crosland, Gaitskell, but also Tom Mboya, people from the Left overseas; had debates ab
o
ut NATO; had debates about the bomb. A huge centre for political discussion. And only after that were there clubs of a similar kind started elsewhere among readers. The Partisan was really a sort of offshoot of the Club. Instead of hiring these places, wh
y don\rquote t we have a place of our own? Well, we could only afford, with the people that Raphael rustled up contributions from, a very small place, though in Soho - can you imagine, the corner of Soho Square, I mean a really a prize site, but that
\rquote s all we could [afford]. But where we going to hold these Club meetings? Sometimes we had 300 people there. Well, there was a plan that there was a basement, and the basement is where Raphael\rquote 
s penchant for small tables with chess - one or two people like Quentin ?? what\rquote s his name \'85
 took root down there, and never seen again! (LAUGHS) He had one cup of coffee, and endless chess games. But it was not very big. Upstairs was the main room where the tables were, but where to put a speaker? Where would you put Deutscher? There\rquote 
s a sort of platform going downstairs, if you sited Deutscher on the platform, the downstairs people could see his feet, and the upstairs people would see his head and down to his waist! (LAUGHS) So we never held meetings there. We had to go on hiring 
places elsewhere. But that was the beginnings of The Partisan. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7739222\charrsid7739222 
