\par Stuart:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3228552\charrsid3228552 Well, I\rquote ll say something about them. She was a South African Trotskyist family \endash 
 refugee from South Africa, and he was a paid-up working-class, militant, Trotskyist, and they had this big house in Clapham, which I got a room in, along with other students, and they became my 
sort of substitute family. So I was there, and I got a job in Kennington, or the Oval. And they took me on \endash  in those days, supply teachers didn\rquote t have to have any training, nobody was going to ask me, could I teach? }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7739222\charrsid7739222 
