\par Stuart:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3228552\charrsid3228552 No. No, no, no, there were black kids from Brixton. But, from going furth
er round, from Kennington, Clapham. But not the majority by any means, not like a contemporary inner city school with the majority black population, nothing like that. Remember, this is the early stage of black settlement. The first period of settling in,
 then the emergence of areas of high enough migration to constitute sort of colonies, like Notting Hill, or like Tottenham, it\rquote s just the beginning of that. There\rquote s no active black politics, so it\rquote s a very different world. There
\rquote s no visibility of black peo
ple inthe media, public affairs, the newspapers, public offices, shops - none. Just beginning. Just beginning. The Windrush generation in the course of discovering that they, too, like me, are not going home, so a life has to begin here, and a life eventu
ally emerges. But in 1957, \rquote 58, it\rquote s not yet that in a fully articulated way. North Kensington and Brixton were sort of the first of those obvious settlements that I became aware of. Brixton\rquote 
s an older established one, where people who had volunteered for the War, and stayed, or come back because they didn\rquote 
t like it at home, settled, so it had an older West Indian population, and Notting Hill, which was the transients - people who had come later, not brought their families, or brought their family, living in
 one room, multi-occupation, all of that, and it became a different kind of West Indian settlement. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7739222\charrsid7739222 
\par 
\par Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3228552\charrsid3228552 You were saying you taught them English as one the main subjects, and what kind of English did you teach \endash 
 apart from the grammar? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7739222\charrsid7739222 
\par 
\par Stuart:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3228552\charrsid3228552 Well, mainly language and writing, writing stories. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7739222\charrsid7739222 
