volved in the early New Left. We staged the discussion which is in ULR, between Raymond Williams and Hoggart, so when he got the money to start Birmingham, he asked me if I wanted to come and be a Research Fellow to set up some kind of group, research gro
up, that would work in this area, extending the analysis of use of literacy, and that approach, rather than making him do supervisions in traditional literary subjects. And I said yes. I gave up Chelsea. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
