 And when it occurred to me that really the underlying context, was her place in the family, and the role of the family in relation to her, and all of that - she\rquote 
s a kind of victim of the colonial dependency which was characteristic of my upbringing, my family background \endash  they wouldn\rquote 
t let her marry a black man. The distillation of the whole culture in this personal familial crisis was what fascinated me, because I knew it wasn\rquote t a simple question that \'93she\rquote s suffering from this\'94. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
