\par Stuart:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3228552\charrsid3228552 I did start, I did start to read Freud, yes, then. And she had shock therapy, given by people who really weren\rquote 
t at all experienced in it, ordinary, I think, GPs or medical people. So I was anxious to puzzle it out, so I started reading Freud, yes. When I discovered what psychoanalysis was, I thought, \'93Well, maybe this is what you should do?\'94
 But I then thought I would need to be trained medically in order to do it, I couldn\rquote 
t think that you could make a living at it in Jamaica, and I was intending to go back. But if I were medically trained, I could have then specialised in mental illness or something like that. But that would mean doing sciences a
t school, so I could get into medical school, and I wasn\rquote t really very good or interested in that, so I gave it up. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7739222\charrsid7739222 
