t get a group like that together, meeting week after week, reading together, debating together, until it starts to produce itself, so some of these groups started to produce joint work. The History Group looked at 
the influence of Marxist historians in the Historians Group, so it went into that in depth, so it had something to say about that. \'93
Well, what are you going to do with this? This is not your thesis, but emerges out of the group work that you have done for your thesis\'94. \'93Well, perhaps you ought to publish some of them for each other, because over there there\rquote 
s a Media Group, you don\rquote t know what they\rquote re doing. And over there is a Deviancy Group, you don\rquote t know what they\rquote re doing and what they\rquote re reading. So y
ou ought to tell each other, so write a paper, or summarise the work of the Group for the year or the term, so you have to have a session where each Group reports what it\rquote s been doing,\'94 because you\rquote 
re still in the business of creating a common conversation around cultural studies. You\rquote 
re aware that cultural studies is this hybrid field of studies, not a discipline. But they have to understand each other in order to constitute something more than particular specialisms in each area. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
