\par Stuart:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3228552\charrsid3228552 Well, a whole range of women. I\rquote m not going to be good on names because my memory is so poor. Rachel Powell, Angela, there
\rquote s [Charlotte Brunsdon], who was working on jobs, employment. A lot of people who were doing other kinds of cognate research were from, o
ne point or another, members of the discussion around Resistance to Rituals. After all, they were not all from a single class background, but they were all the product of emerging youth culture. They all knew about women\rquote 
s magazines, and they all knew about rock music, and they all were familiar with those questions which formed the background to Resistance to Rituals, and then some of the questions we started to ask in Policing the Crisis. So it wasn\rquote 
t a group with a permanent membership, it was a loose agglomeration, out of which the four of us - the four of them and myself \endash 
 decided to take the research much further on. Yes? Go more deeply into it. And then we decided to produce some papers together, written together \endash  not separately authored \endash  and then w
e decided to try and find somebody who was interested in a book, which we did, and we decided to author that book collectively. So the research is from 1972, and it\rquote s not published until 1978. I mean, Paul, I say this often to you, but it\rquote 
s quite hard to communicate how open-ended the project was. We were in the process of institutionalising a field of study Yes? So the structures were loose enough to allow us to do, really, what we liked. People say, \'93Well, why isn\rquote 
t there a Centre for Cultural Studies now?\'94
 No university or higher education institution would allow a sort of grouping like that to develop independently, upstairs, doing what they liked, reading what they liked, organising themselves as they liked, but productive: producing papers, producing r
esearch, doing theses. You can\rquote t quarrel with that. But what is going on up there? So, you know, that\rquote s the moment before the institutionalisation of graduate studies in English higher education, we\rquote 
re just at the edge of that, so it really was improvisatory. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7739222\charrsid7739222 
