\par Stuart:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3228552\charrsid3228552 I didn\rquote 
t come in with an overall plan to change it. We were already in such an improvisational and innovatory frame of mind, and I thought, \'93Let\rquote s go on just doing this\'94. What I did
 do was to take in the two new members of staff into that planning bit \endash  Richard (Johnson) and Michael Green \endash  and then to add the most senior researcher, to some extent \endash 
 Paul Willis. Although Paul was never really involved in Centre organisation, but he 
was a slightly senior figure, published a book, then done substantial research, published another book, so he was in between the ordinary general students and the leadership. So I didn\rquote t have a plan, but we met regularly to talk about - \'93There
\rquote s this problem\'94. \'93How should we change that?\'94 \'93Shall we institute a new Group?\'94
 etc.. Then we also had a general Centre Planning Meeting, which every student took part in, in which the weekly organisation of the research, questions of what the curriculum might be in the theory course \endash 
 everything was discussed. Everything. So it was a very participatory structure which, again, was something which couldn\rquote t have happened outside of that period. Very participatory. So I didn\rquote t have a plan. A lot of planning was going on, 
but it was of a rather loose collective kind, not my plan imposed on it, shaping it from the beginning. I accepted that I had a slightly different set of interests from Richard\rquote s or Michael\rquote 
s, but we shared enough. I had a different theoretical orientation from them. Richard was, at that stage, a very committed Thompsonian \endash  social historian. Michael Green was coming strongly from literary criticism \endash 
 which was my own background, but I was no longer really working in that field \endash  etc., etc.. So we had our d
ifferent spheres of interest, but we all were committed to the project of constituting a centre of research and theory building, in this area, in the Centre. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7739222\charrsid7739222 
