\par Stuart:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3228552\charrsid3228552 Well, I got interested in the visual arts. I had been interested, as I said, as a child - as a young person - because part of my 
intellectual awakening was to see Picasso for the first time, and to see Paul Klee for the first time, and to see Cezanne and wonder what the relationship is between the two, and to see Braque, so this bursts on me like an incredible new world. And it doe
sn\rquote t look like the things they\rquote re supposed to, people don\rquote t look like that! (LAUGHS) Picasso is seeing them from the front and the side at the same time, what sense does that make, in terms of real time? Okay. So it\rquote 
s part of my awakening in that sense. I\rquote m interested in it, but I\rquote m not a student of the visual arts \endash  then, or, indeed, later. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7739222\charrsid7739222 
