\par Stuart:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3228552\charrsid3228552 Well, it\rquote s not a cultural organisation like that, I don\rquote 
t think. It has a narrower purpose. It says anybody who is interested in the question of how are black people represented, and how do they represent themselves, will find interesting work and interesting artists in this building. It\rquote 
s not only black, of course. Rivington Place is for cultural diversity, because by then, \'93cultural diversity\'94 is the term which has come in, because it needs to cover Caribbean, Asian, Pakistani, Indian, so by then it\rquote 
s not limited to black culture as such. And it\rquote s not a cultural roots organisation \endash  do you understand what I\rquote 
m saying? You know, there are organisations which invest - carnival. Yes? The Committee that started carnival is really an investment in the community itself. Rivington Place was not intending to do that, it
 was more narrowly conceived in relation to new developments in the visual arts \endash  photography, design, etc.. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7739222\charrsid7739222 
