t want to. It\rquote s not because Derrida isn\rquote t important, although I think a lot of Derrida is nonsense, but it\rquote s because I don\rquote 
t aspire to do that kind of work. But I do aspire to do work that combines the concrete and the conceptual. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7739222\charrsid7739222 
