\par Stuart:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3228552\charrsid3228552 Well, through music, through going as often as I could, but mainly, as I think I said to you in the very first interv
iew, through the diaspora. If I couldn\rquote t bear to live there, and I couldn\rquote t bear to give it up, I became a diasporic subject, so I lived it in relation to the connection the diaspora opened up. Music, fashion, young people - everything. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7739222\charrsid7739222 
