\par Stuart:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3228552\charrsid3228552 
So he married to Radha [Singh], and Rada is from Rajasthan, herself a product of an English/Indian parentage, who went to school in England, and he met her at St. Martin\rquote 
s. And they have one boy, who is my beloved Ishan. They are currently living in Santa Monica, because after Jess shot his last film his American agent said, \'93Come. We can get you work\'94 etc.. So they\rquote ve gone to try. They\rquote ve been ther
e a little less than a year. I don\rquote t know how long they\rquote ll stay, or whether they\rquote ll stay for good. We just don\rquote t know. So that\rquote s what he\rquote s doing. He\rquote 
s shot a film, that you would never have seen, but which was a complete youth ray, called Hot Fuzz; he shot a very nice film about young people trying to make a movie, getting a camera and trying to make a movie; and he\rquote 
s shot the Darwin film called Resurrection, is it? Recreation? And he\rquote s shot a second version of Brideshead Revisited; and I told you he shot a Marley film. He\rquote 
s made a film in South Africa, which is about South African policemen who shot a guy at a demonstration, converted to the ANC, who was a bank robber. So he\rquote s made a variety of films. He filmed with Jennifer Aniston in New York, a year and 
a half ago. He\rquote 
s looking for the right kind of script, with the right kind of director; meanwhile, working on commercials, all over the world, after they went to America, in order to be able to live at home longer in the year. Because he was away from both
 his son and from Rada, for I suppose, three-quarters of the year, because during his career it\rquote s been too expensive to make advertisements in England, so he\rquote 
s always sort of in Tokyo and Ecuador, or Poland, Czechoslovakia. So he has rather a peripatetic life, which doesn\rquote t suit him, but that\rquote 
s how he makes the money. Whereas my daughter, Becky, had a long relationship with a French[man]. My daughter has a strong taste for the vulnerable and the deviant, so she\rquote s had some strange boyfriends! In the past, sh
e took up with this guy, he was quite a nice guy, but really seriously in trouble personally. They had one boy, who is my beloved grandson, Noah, who\rquote s now 13, and says he\rquote s French/Jamaican English! (LAUGHS) But Becky and Amaury \endash 
 that\rquote s his name, Breton name \endash 
 broke up some while ago, quite a long while ago, because as she became more involved in clinical work, young people, children and parents in trouble, he was less interested in all that, and she decided, I think, that their lives diverged so much, wasn
\rquote t going to make a go of it. And now her partner, currently, is a young man - I say \'93young man\'94, they\rquote re both in their early forties, who works with youth work \endash 
 Simon, with a son the same age as Noah. Noah is my - I love both of my grandsons dearly, and they\rquote 
re very different. Ishan is studious, inquisitive, social. Noah is strong-willed, makes up his mind, chooses what he wants to do with an adamantan will, and nothing is going to move him, etc.. A rather more difficult boy. But I adore him! And I adore 
him because Becky and Amoury tried to buy a flat, and she was pregnant, and that didn\rquote t come off, and when she had Noah, they came to live in our house, so I changed Noah\rquote 
s nappies, sat him right here at this table, where he pulled this drawer, and left it open, aged 5 months or 10 months. So I\rquote m very close to both of them, in different ways. Two boys. Sorry I didn\rquote t have a girl. So is Catherine. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7739222\charrsid7739222 
